DCC May Buy Irish Unit of Premier Foods, Sunday Times Reports

-- B y   F i n b a r r   F l y n n
-- 
2011-12-11T09:28:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-11/dcc-may-buy-irish-unit-of-premier-foods-sunday-times-reports.html
DCC Plc (DCC)  is close to acquiring
 Premier Foods Plc (PFD) ’s Irish division, the Sunday Times  reported ,
without saying where it got the information.  Boyne Valley Foods and Valeo Foods are also interested in
buying the unit of the British food company, the Sunday Times
said. The business has been expected to sell for between 30
million euros and 40 million euros ($40 million to $54 million),
the London-based newspaper said in its Irish edition.  A spokesman for DCC couldn’t be contacted for comment
outside regular office hours. DCC declined to comment on the
report, the Sunday Times said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Finbarr Flynn in Dublin at 
 fflynn3@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at   ckeatinge@bloomberg.net  